body:
GRContext.Create always returns null. There is no hint what is the error. Through testing I found that if I disable 3D Acceleration for Virtual Box the context gets created. The project uses OpenTK for OpenGL. Under windows the combination works just fine. What makes me wondering is that there is no error message, nothing. The GRContext is just null.

Code versions i tried:

```
var glInterface = GRGlInterface.CreateNativeGlInterface();
var grContext = GRContext.Create(GRBackend.OpenGL, glInterface);

// or
var grContext = GRContext.Create(GRBackend.OpenGL);

// or
OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContext.Assert();
var context = OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContext.CurrentContext;
var internalContext = (OpenTK.Graphics.IGraphicsContextInternal)context;
var xglinterface = GRGlInterface.AssembleGlInterface((obj, name) => internalContext.GetAddress(name));
var grContext = GRContext.Create(GRBackend.OpenGL, xglinterface);
```

VBox 5.2.8
Debian 9
Mono 5.10.1.20
NuGet Package of SkiaSharp 1.6.0

*.so files from SkiaSharp copied.

OpenTK itself works. Direct rendering is active in OpenTK, same for glxinfo output.
